body:
@abaveja313 I was able to reproduce this issue by deploying a PySpark model with the same conda environment you provided on a `ml.t2.medium` instance. 

Deploying on a larger instance, such as the default `ml.m4.xlarge` succeeds. My suspicion is that the limited network bandwidth on smaller t2 instances causes large delays during conda environment resolution; perhaps this is leading to a timeout. I will continue to investigate the issue to reach a more concrete conclusion. In the mean time, can you try deploying on a larger instance?

**Update**: It seems that deployment also succeeds on `ml.t2.large` and `ml.t2.xlarge` instances. `ml.t2.medium` is the only problematic worker type that I've encountered thus far.
